:: Admited obs for ACS Symptoms {"position":"3900,3300","size":"100,100"}
ACS-- Acute Coronary Syndrome is an umbrella  term ranging from stable angina to STEMI. 
Although the physician may list ACS on this patients diagnosis, this patient is not appropriate for observation. 
With an elevated troponin and active symptoms (epigastric pain and vomiting), this patient would need to be assigned in an inpatient status bed. 

Take a look at the differences in these possible ACS disgnosis 

 {<div  style="overflow:scroll">
<img
src=https://img.grepmed.com/uploads/3707/diagnosis-angina-nstemi-definitions-acs-original.jpeg
width="2000" height="600"
</div>}

Let's take another look at the possible [[resources they need]].


