:: Discharge home with follow up by cardiology {"position":"3875,3025","size":"100,100"}
This patient should not be discharged home. 
There is an elevated troponin with no alternative cause. You should be hesitant to send home any patient with newly elevated troponin, especially in absence of kidney disfunction. 
Let's take another look at the possible [[resources they need]] before they go home.


