:: LAD {"position":"2550,2975","size":"100,100"}
#(text-style:"bold","wavy-underline","outline")[CORRECT]

#Left Anterior Descending Artery
This large vessle provides about 50% of your hearts blood supply. 
The nickname for this vessel is the "Widowmaker" 
{<div  style="overflow:scroll"
class="image-container">
<img
src=https://my.clevelandclinic.org/-/scassets/images/org/health/articles/24507-widowmaker-heart-attack-illustration
width="550" height="1450"
<div class="overlay-text"
</div>}

---
Notice how on the image below, the precordial leads are placed anatomically directly over the vessles descending from the LAD. 
This image stresses the important of accurate lead placement when preforming EKG


{<div style="overflow:scroll">
<img
src=https://ecgwaves.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/09/ecg-localization-myocardial-infarction-stemi-ischemia-coronary-artery-occlusion.jpg
width="700" height="500"
</div>}

---


